2:Ta4e,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much space do I need for a sliding gate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You need clear space along your boundary wall or fence equal to the width of the gate opening, plus about 500mm. So if your driveway entrance is 4 metres wide, you need roughly 4.5 metres of unobstructed wall to one side. Our installers will measure during the site survey and advise on any adjustments needed."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can a sliding gate work on a sloped driveway?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, but it takes careful planning. Sliding gates run on a ground track, so the track needs to be level even if the driveway itself slopes. Experienced installers can work with gradients by adjusting the track bed and using cantilever systems for steeper sites. This is something to discuss at the survey stage."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does a sliding gate installation take?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most residential sliding gate installations in London take 2 to 4 days. Day one covers groundwork, track laying, and post installation. Day two is the gate itself and automation. Days three and four, if needed, handle finishing, intercom wiring, and final testing. Complex sites or bespoke designs may take a day or two longer."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does a driveway gate installation take?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most standard installations take 2 to 4 days from start to finish. Day one is typically groundwork and post installation. Day two is the gate fitting and automation wiring. Bespoke or complex projects may take up to a week. Your installer will give you a clear timeline during the site survey."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need planning permission for driveway gates?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In most cases, no. Driveway gates under 2 metres tall that open inward generally fall under permitted development. However, if your property is listed, in a conservation area, or the gate is next to a classified road, you may need approval. Your installer will advise on any planning requirements during the survey."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What warranty should I expect?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Reputable installers offer a minimum 2-year warranty on the motor and automation, and 5 to 10 years on the gate structure and finish. Some premium manufacturers offer 25-year guarantees on materials like aluminium or Accoya wood. Always check the warranty terms before committing to a quote."}}]}5:["serviceSlug","electric-sliding-gates","d"]
